article_title: NYC Park Goes to the Dogs for Halloween Parade
article_text: Hundreds of costumed dogs descended on a New York City park Saturday for what was billed as the nation's largest Halloween dog parade. Thousands of spectators mingled with about 300 four-legged contestants in Manhattan's Tompkins Square Park. (Oct. AP
